big.ij.snake3D
Interface Snake3D

public interface Snake3D

This abstract class encapsulates the number-crunching aspect of snakes.

See Also:
Snake3DKeeper, Snake3DNode

Method Detail

energy

double energy()
The purpose of this method is to compute the energy of the snake. This energy is usually made of three additive terms: 1) the image energy, which gives the driving force associated to the data; 2) the internal energy, which favors smoothness of the snake; and 3) the constraint energy, which incorporates a priori knowledge. This method is called repeatedly during the optimization of the snake, but only as long as the method isAlive() returns true. It is imperative that this function be everywhere differentiable with respect to the snake-defining nodes.

Returns:
Return a number that should attain a minimal value when the snake is optimal. Negative values are admissible.
See Also:
isAlive()

getEnergyGradient

javax.vecmath.Point3d[] getEnergyGradient()
The purpose of this method is to compute the gradient of the snake energy with respect to the snake-defining nodes. This method is called repeatedly during the optimization of the snake, but only as long as the method isAlive() returns true. The optimization takes place under the control of the methods Snake3DKeeper.optimize() and Snake3DKeeper.interactAndOtimize().

Returns:
Return an array that contains the gradient values associated to each node. They predict the variation of the energy for a horizontal or vertical displacement of one pixel. The ordering of the nodes must follow that of getNodes(). If null is returned, the optimizer within the class Snake3DKeeper will attempt to estimate the gradient by a finite-difference approach.
See Also:
Snake3DKeeper.optimize(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), getNodes(), isAlive()

getNodes

Snake3DNode[] getNodes()
This method provides an accessor to the snake-defining nodes. It may be called unconditionally, whether the method isAlive() returns true or false.

Returns:
Return an array of subpixel node locations. It is expected that the ordering of the nodes and the number of nodes does not change during the lifetime of the snake.
See Also:
setNodes(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3DNode[])

getScales

Snake3DScale[] getScales(int sliceIndex)
The purpose of this method is to detemine what to draw on screen, given the current configuration of nodes. This method is called repeatedly during the user interaction provided by the method Snake3DKeeper.interact(). It may also be called from the method Snake3DKeeper.optimize() if its display parameter is not null. It is not called if the method isAlive() returns false. The origin of coordinates lies at the top-left corner of the display parameter. Collectively, the array of scales forms the skin of the snake.

Parameters:
sliceIndex - Index of the slice that will be adorned.
Returns:
Return an array of Snake3DScale objects. Straight lines will be drawn between the apices of each polygon, in the specified color. It is not necessary to maintain a constant number of polygons in the array, or a constant number of apices in a given polygon.
See Also:
Snake3DScale, Snake3DKeeper.interact(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), Snake3DKeeper.optimize(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), isAlive()

isAlive

boolean isAlive()
The purpose of this method is to monitor the status of the snake. One of its uses is to unconditionally abort the method Snake3DKeeper.optimize() by returning false, which provides an easy way to limit the number of optimization steps by counting the number of calls to the method energy(). Another use is to promote the abortion of the method Snake3DKeeper.interact(); the abortion request will be honored at the next user attempt to modify the snake.

Returns:
Return true if the snake could be properly initialized, if the skin contain valid data, and if the energy and its gradient can be computed; else, return false.
See Also:
energy(), getEnergyGradient(), getScales(int), Snake3DKeeper.interact(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), Snake3DKeeper.optimize(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus)

setNodes

void setNodes(Snake3DNode[] node)
This method provides a mutator to the snake-defining nodes. It will be called repeatedly by the methods Snake3DKeeper.interact() and Snake3DKeeper.optimize(). These calls are unconditional and may happen whether the method isAlive() returns true or false.

Parameters:
node - Array of subpixel node locations.
See Also:
getNodes(), Snake3DKeeper.interact(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), Snake3DKeeper.optimize(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus)

updateStatus

void updateStatus(boolean canceledByUser,
                  boolean snakeDied,
                  boolean optimalSnakeFound,
                  java.lang.Double energy)
This method is called when the methods Snake3DKeeper.interact(), Snake3DKeeper.interactAndOptimize(), and Snake3DKeeper.optimize() are about to terminate. It provides a report on the current status of this snake.

Parameters:
canceledByUser - If true, indicates that the user chose to interactively abort the processing of the snake. Otherwise, if false, indicates that the dealings with the snake were terminated without user assistance.
snakeDied - Result of the last call made to the method isAlive().
optimalSnakeFound - If true, indicates that the last array of nodes sent to the method setNodes() was optimal in the sense of the method energy(). Otherwise, if false, indicates the the optimization either did not proceed at all or was aborted.
energy - If null, indicates that the keeper released the snake during an interactive session. Else, contains the lowest energy found so far during optimization.
See Also:
Snake3DKeeper.interact(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), Snake3DKeeper.interactAndOptimize(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), Snake3DKeeper.optimize(big.ij.snake3D.Snake3D, ij.ImagePlus), isAlive()
